**Why didn't exploitation occur?**

Hypothesis: **The mutation operator is too constrained.**

Current `DocstringMutator` only changes:
- Style (formal/casual/technical) =20
- Detail level (brief/moderate/verbose)

It NEVER modifies the template text itself. So even though TriggerWordEvaluat=
or would reward trigger words, the search has no mechanism to add them!

**This reveals a key insight:**

Quality-diversity search can only exploit evaluators within the **reachable m=
utation space**. The evaluator bias exists, but the mutations don't explore t=
he vulnerable region.

This is actually GOOD for robustness but BAD for our demonstration.

